snippet.description:
Click here to Subscribe to Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah Official Channel: https://www.youtube.com/taarakmehtakaooltahchashmah?sub_confirmation=1 

Click here to watch all your favorite Episode videos: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gqFEadNxmd8&list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu 

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Shailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi / Raj Anadkat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Cast:
---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada
Raj Anadkat / Bhavya Gandhi as Tipendra Jethalal Gada (Tapu) 
Amit Bhatt as Champaklal Jayantilal Gada
Shailesh Lodha as Taarak Mehta
Neha Mehta as Anjali Taarak Mehta
Tanuj Mahashabde as Krishnan Subramaniam Iyer

Mandar Chandwadkar as Aatmaram Tukaram Bhide

Nidhi Bhanushali / Palak Sidhwani as Sonalika Aatmaram Bhide (Sonu) 
Gurucharan Singh as Roshan Singh Harjeet Singh Sodhi
Jennifer Mistry Bansiwal as Roshan Kaur Roshan Singh Sodhi
Kavi Kumar Azad / Nirmal Soni as Dr. Hansraj Hathi 
Ambika Ranjankar as Komal Hansraj Hathi
Kush Shah as Gulabkumar Hansraj Hathi (Goli)
Shyam Pathak as Popatlal Pandey
Sharad Sankla as Abdul
Azhar Shaikh as Pinku

snippet.description:
Click here to Subscribe to Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah Official Channel: https://www.youtube.com/taarakmehtakaooltahchashmah?sub_confirmation=1 

Click here to watch all your favorite Episode videos: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gqFEadNxmd8&list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu 

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Shailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi / Raj Anadkat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Cast:
---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada
Raj Anadkat / Bhavya Gandhi as Tipendra Jethalal Gada (Tapu) 
Amit Bhatt as Champaklal Jayantilal Gada
Shailesh Lodha as Taarak Mehta

Ambika Ranjankar as Komal Hansraj Hathi

Azhar Shaikh as Pinku

snippet.title: Free Training and Job!!! | DDU GKY | Dreamz Unlimited
snippet.description:
DDU-GKY was launched on 25 September 2014 .The Vision of DDU-GKY is to "Transform rural poor youth into an economically independent and globally relevant workforce". It aims to target youth, in the age group of 15‚Äì35 years. DDU-GKY is a part of the National Rural Livelihood Mission (NRLM), tasked with the dual objectives of adding diversity to the incomes of rural poor families and cater to the career aspirations of rural youth. A corpus of Rs 1,500 crore is aimed at enhancing the employ ability of rural youth. Under this programme, disbursements would be made through a digital voucher directly into the student‚Äôs bank account as part of the government's skill development initiative. Kaushalpanjee.nic.in
For more information contact - +91 6009692907

Shoot Location - Jakhama Village, Kohima, Nagaland.

snippet.title: Armenia-Azerbaijan conflict: Azerbaijan president vows to fight on - BBC News
snippet.description:
Azerbaijan's president has vowed to fight on until Armenian forces leave disputed territory, on the fourth day of fierce fighting in the region.
"We only have one condition: Armenian armed forces must unconditionally, fully, and immediately leave our lands," President Ilham Aliyev said.
More than 100 deaths have been reported in the heaviest fighting in years over the Nagorno-Karabakh region.
Officially part of Azerbaijan, it is governed by ethnic Armenians.
The two former Soviet republics fought a war in 1988-1994 over the territory. Although Armenia backs the self-declared republic it has never officially recognised it.
#BBCOS #BBCOutsideSource

The 74-year-old said the couple were self-isolating after Hope Hicks, one of his top aides, tested positive.

snippet.title: Wolverine Arrives | Fortnite
snippet.description:
Battle Pass owners, the Wolverine Outfit and Classic Style is available now! Read more here: https://fn.gg/Wolverine

He's the best at what he does, but what he does isn't very nice.

You‚Äôve already seen Weapon X working behind the scenes, and with Fortnite‚Äôs Chapter 2 - Season 4 Battle Pass, you can now unlock (and unleash) Wolverine. Prove you‚Äôre not a bub in Wolverine‚Äôs new Challenge for you!

Unlocking the Wolverine Outfit is just scratching the surface. Take action in Wolverine‚Äôs other Battle Pass Challenges and get your hands on more Wolverine rewards, like Wolverine‚Äôs Trophy Back Bling and Ferocious Wrap. 

After unlocking his Outfit, complete Wolverine‚Äôs special request and unlock his built-in Snikt! Emote. Trigger it to replace your Pickaxe with his classic Adamantium Claws. Swap back and forth anytime between the Adamantium Claws and the Pickaxe you have equipped!


Play Fortnite Battle Royale, the completely free 100-player PvP mode. One giant map, A Battle Bus, Last one standing wins. ESRB Rating: Teen with Violence.

snippet.title: ZooPhobia - "Bad Luck Jack" (Short)
snippet.description:
Musical score by Gooseworx!
Enjoy this cartoon about Jack, a sweet pup with supernatural bad luck -as he lets his best friend Zill help him with his curse, for better or worse!

Set in the fantasy world of the 2012 webcomic "ZooPhobia" by Vivienne M.
BASED on the comic's characters!

Thank you everyone who supported on patreon or via merch sales! We are so glad we can bring you more cartoon content, and look forward to more HELLUVA BOSS very very soon!

MERCH: https://sharkrobot.com/collections/vivziepop

Or Support us on Patreon!

snippet.title: The Infinite Pattern That Never Repeats
snippet.description:
Simples rules of geometry meant that 5-fold symmetry was impossible as were crystals without a periodic structure. This turns out to be wrong. Thanks to LastPass for sponsoring a portion of this video. Click here to start using LastPass: https://ve42.co/LPs

Huge thanks to Prof. Paul Steinhardt for the interview on this topic. Check out his book ‚ÄòThe Second Kind of Impossible‚Äô

If you'd like to learn more about Penrose tilings, go check out "Penrose Tiles to Trapdoor Ciphers" by Martin Gardener, which helped my research for this video.

Filmed by Gene Nagata (Potato Jet on YouTube)
Animations by Iv√°n Tello and Jonny Hyman
Editing, Coloring, Music & Audio mastering by Jonny Hyman

Prague scenes filmed in 2012.
Special thanks to Raquel Nuno for helping with the tilings!

Additional Music from Epidemic Sound

snippet.title: Ecco the Dolphin (Sega Genesis) - Angry Video Game Nerd (AVGN)
snippet.description:
AVGN 1&2 Deluxe coming October 30th to Nintendo Switch and Steam!!
New Merch Store: https://store.cinemassacre.com
Wishlist on Steam: https://store.steampowered.com/app/1162960/Angry_Video_Game_Nerd_I__II_Deluxe/
Coming later to PlayStation and Xbox stores!!

Angry Video Game Nerd (AVGN) episode 183: Ecco the Dolphin. Ecco is an action-adventure game originally developed by Ed Annunziata and Novotrade International for the Sega Genesis and published by Sega in 1992. The original game followed the exploits of a young dolphin named Ecco as he searched the seas, and eventually time itself, for his missing pod. The game is known for being super unique with a great art style, but it's also known for being hard, frustrating, and unfair.

snippet.title: Is It Too Late To Stop Climate Change? Well, it's Complicated.
snippet.description:
This video is part of a series about climate change supported by Breakthrough Energy ‚Äì a coalition founded by Bill Gates, that is working to expand clean-energy investment and support the innovations that will lead the world to net-zero carbon emissions. 
https://www.gatesnotes.com/Climate-and-energy?WT.mc_id=20200625100000_ClimateCtr2020_CTRKurt-YT_&WT.tsrc=CTRKurtYT

Also a special thanks to the team at Our World for helping us out with data and research!
https://ourworldindata.org/

Sources & further reading:
https://sites.google.com/view/sources-climate-solve/

Climate Change is just too much. There is never any good news. Only graphs that get more and more red and angry. Almost every year breaks some horrible record, from the harshest heat waves to the most rapid Glacier melt. It‚Äôs endless and relentless. 

We have known for decades that rapid Climate Change is being caused by the release of Greenhouse Gases. But instead of reducing them, in 2019 the world was emitting 50% more CO2 than in the year 2000. And emissions are still rising. Why is that? Why is it  so hard to just stop emitting these gases?

localizations.en-GB.description:
This video is part of a series about climate change supported by Breakthrough Energy ‚Äì a coalition founded by Bill Gates, that is working to expand clean-energy investment and support the innovations that will lead the world to net-zero carbon emissions. 
https://www.gatesnotes.com/Climate-and-energy?WT.mc_id=20200625100000_ClimateCtr2020_CTRKurt-YT_&WT.tsrc=CTRKurtYT

Also a special thanks to the team at Our World for helping us out with data and research!
https://ourworldindata.org/

Sources & further reading:
https://sites.google.com/view/sources-climate-solve/

Climate Change is just too much. There is never any good news. Only graphs that get more and more red and angry. Almost every year breaks some horrible record, from the harshest heat waves to the most rapid Glacier melt. It‚Äôs endless and relentless. 

We have known for decades that rapid Climate Change is being caused by the release of Greenhouse Gases. But instead of reducing them, in 2019 the world was emitting 50% more CO2 than in the year 2000. And emissions are still rising. Why is that? Why is it  so hard to just stop emitting these gases?

Il cambiamento climatico √® ormai ovunque. Non c'√® mai una buona notizia. Solo grafici sempre pi√π in rosso. Quasi ogni anno vengono infranti orribili primati, dall'ondata di caldo pi√π estrema allo scioglimento di ghiacciai pi√π veloce. √à senza fine ed implacabile.

Abbiamo saputo per decadi che il rapido cambiamento climatico √® causato dall'emissione dei gas serra. Ma invece di ridurli, nel 2019 il mondo ha prodotto il 50% di CO2 in pi√π rispetto all'anno 2000. E le emissioni continuano a crescere. Perch√© accade tutto ci√≤? localizations.af.title: Is dit te laat om klimaatsverandering te stop? Wel, dit is ingewikkeld.
localizations.af.description:
Hierdie video is deel van 'n reeks oor klimaatsverandering wat ondersteun word deur Breakthrough Energy - 'n koalisie wat gestig is deur Bill Gates, wat werk om beleggings in skoon energie uit te brei en die innovasies te ondersteun wat die w√™reld tot koolstofvrystelling sal lei.
https://www.gatesnotes.com/Climate-and-energy?WT.mc_id=20200625100000_ClimateCtr2020_CTRKurt-YT_&WT.tsrc=CTRKurtYT

Ook 'n spesiale dank aan die span van Our World vir die hulp met data en navorsing!
https://ourworldindata.org/

Bronne en verdere leeswerk:
https://sites.google.com/view/sources-climate-solve/

Klimaatsverandering is net te veel. Daar is nooit goeie nuus nie. Slegs grafieke wat al hoe meer rooi en kwaad word. Byna elke jaar breek die een of ander verskriklike rekord, van die felste hittegolwe tot die vinnigste smelt van die gletser. Dit is eindeloos en meedo√´nloos.

Ons weet al dekades lank dat vinnige klimaatsverandering veroorsaak word deur die vrystelling van kweekhuisgasse. Maar in plaas daarvan om dit te verminder, het die w√™reld in 2019 50% meer CO2 vrygestel as in die jaar 2000. En die uitstoot neem steeds toe. Hoekom is dit? Waarom is dit so moeilik om net op te hou om hierdie gasse uit te straal?

localizations.nl.title: Is Het Te Laat Om Klimaatverandering Te Stoppen? Nou, Het Is Ingewikkeld.
localizations.nl.description:
Deze video maakt deel uit van een serie over klimaatverandering die wordt ondersteund door Breakthrough Energy - een coalitie die is opgericht door Bill Gates, die zich inzet om investeringen in schone energie uit te breiden en de innovaties te ondersteunen die de wereld naar een netto nul-uitstoot van koolstof zullen leiden.

Klimaatverandering is gewoon te veel. Er is nooit goed nieuws. Alleen grafieken die steeds roder en bozer worden. Bijna elk jaar breekt een vreselijk record, van de zwaarste hittegolven tot de snelste smeltende gletsjer. Het is eindeloos en meedogenloos. 

We weten al decennia dat de snelle klimaatverandering wordt veroorzaakt door het vrijkomen van broeikasgassen. Maar in plaats van ze te verminderen, stootte de wereld in 2019 50% meer CO2 uit dan in het jaar 2000. En de uitstoot stijgt nog steeds. Waarom is dat? Waarom is het zo moeilijk om gewoon te stoppen met het uitstoten van deze gassen?

snippet.title: Dream vs Technoblade Animation
snippet.description:
Toon Boom Upgrade! :D
This animation took a month and my sanity, I'm not doing this again(maybe sometimes) I'm going back to making animatics. I used a different Techno design because it's fun to experiment a little bit, so I hope you like it (I just want an excuse to animate hair). It wont be my permanent because I also wanted to draw him in his original. His design is inspired by @figgyvevo and @meepbot2 on twitter. There are some scenes I wanna add but the song is too short and I'm lazy and tired.

This animation is based on the video "$100,000 Dream vs Technoblade Duel!":
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zVCs9Cug_qM&t=1s

Music is "Minecraft OST - Pigstep (FlyxTheKid Remix)": https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r_a4Zg3PyA0

Youtubers in this video:
@Dream 
@Technoblade 
@MrBeast Gaming 

Support me on Patreon?? o-o
https://www.patreon.com/SADistfied

And I also have a Discord Server :D
https://t.co/Uw5TF0lfgS?amp=1

snippet.title: Wolverine Arrives | Fortnite
snippet.description:
Battle Pass owners, the Wolverine Outfit and Classic Style is available now! Read more here: https://fn.gg/Wolverine

He's the best at what he does, but what he does isn't very nice.

You‚Äôve already seen Weapon X working behind the scenes, and with Fortnite‚Äôs Chapter 2 - Season 4 Battle Pass, you can now unlock (and unleash) Wolverine. Prove you‚Äôre not a bub in Wolverine‚Äôs new Challenge for you!

Unlocking the Wolverine Outfit is just scratching the surface. Take action in Wolverine‚Äôs other Battle Pass Challenges and get your hands on more Wolverine rewards, like Wolverine‚Äôs Trophy Back Bling and Ferocious Wrap. 

After unlocking his Outfit, complete Wolverine‚Äôs special request and unlock his built-in Snikt! Emote. Trigger it to replace your Pickaxe with his classic Adamantium Claws. Swap back and forth anytime between the Adamantium Claws and the Pickaxe you have equipped!


Play Fortnite Battle Royale, the completely free 100-player PvP mode. One giant map, A Battle Bus, Last one standing wins. ESRB Rating: Teen with Violence.

Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/fortnite/
Twitter: https://twitter.com/FortniteGame
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/FortniteGame/

Learn More: https://www.epicgames.com/fortnite/en-US/

snippet.title: Eric Cartman - "Social Distancing" (Original Music) - SOUTH PARK
snippet.description:
Cartman sings about all the ways the pandemic has made his life better.
Watch "The Pandemic Special" uncensored full episode for free: https://cart.mn/sp-pandemic 

Subscribe to South Park: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC7R27sAWc_DqOldtI1JcYhQ?sub_confirmation=1 

Watch more South Park: https://www.youtube.com/southpark 

About South Park: South Park is the Emmy and Peabody-award winning animated series co-created by Trey Parker and Matt Stone about four boys living in one screwed-up Colorado mountain town. Between local and global tragedies, as well as parental and celebrity interference, Kyle, Stan, Cartman, and Kenny manage to have themselves a time. 

Watch full episodes of South Park: https://cart.mn/episodes 

Shop official South Park merch: https://cart.mn/shop 

Follow South Park: 
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/southpark 
Twitter: https://twitter.com/southpark 
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/southpark 

#SouthPark #PandemicSpecial

EXT. WIDE SHOT - CARTMAN'S HOUSE - MORNING
It's more of a drone point of view wide shot, high angle with a few more houses visible around Cartman's. As if on cue from, Randy's last line, Big theatrical happy music starts to play. 
Then a TITLE FADES up --- 'South Park' and then 'Pandemic Special'
CARTMAN (V.O.)
Wow...
INT. CARTMAN'S ROOM - MORNING 
Cartman is sleeping in his bed when his alarm goes off. His eyes open but he doesn't move. 
HAPPY MUSIC plays as Cartman springs out of bed with a huge smile on his face and walks over to the curtains. 
He THROWS the curtains open excitedly and looks out over the neighborhood. 
CARTMAN
(singing)
Wow! Another day inside!               Don't have to do a thing! 
Cartman turns back to his room, puts out his arms and sings to the heavens-
CARTMAN
I love you social dis-tan-cing! 
Cartman hops back up on his bed, standing on it to sing more. 
CARTMAN
No one's around                   No one's talking to me               Social distancing I'm freee!
INT. CARTMAN'S BATHROOM - SECONDS LATER 
Cartman bursts in the bathroom and gesture towards the sink and shower. 
CARTMAN
Don't have to brush my teeth -       Or shower.  For WHAT???                
Smash cut to Cartman on the toilet reading a comic book. 
CARTMAN
I can sit on the toilet for hours - As much as I want!                          Cuz no one's saying to meeee.     You kids should get outside and do something. 
Cartman's phone alarm goes off and he looks at it.
CARTMAN
Ohp! Nine am! Time for school!
INT. CARTMAN'S ROOM - SECONDS LATER
Cartman happily walks up to the computer and hits some buttons. The music to the song continues underneath. 
BEHIND CARTMAN ON THE COMPUTER SCREEN - The other kids in Cartman's class start to pop up on a zoom call. 
TEACHER
(on zoom)
Good morning guys, everyone ready to start school? 
KIDS
Good morning/Hi Mrs. Davis/Hello/I'm here/etc.
TEACHER
Okay I think we're all here- I see Jimmy and Clyde are on now... ERIC ARE YOU THERE? 
CARTMAN
Yes teacher I'm here! I can't wait to start scho- scho- ep. Ep. Ee. 
As Cartman does this he pretends to be freezing. 
TEACHER
Oh no Eric I think your computer is freezing up again?
CARTMAN
Oh no really? Can you guys hear me? I just said-- Eh. Eh. Eh. Eh. 
Cartman freezes in a pose. 
TEACHER
Eric you'll just have to listen again, okay? Best you can. 
Cartman happily sets an iPad in from of his computer. The iPad has a fullscreen image of frozen Cartman with his eyes closed. 
TEACHER (O.S.)
So let's start today guys, by going over yesterday's grammar examples. Wendy can you read the first one? 
CARTMAN
(singing)
I'm cut off from the world!           Isolated, alone-
On the way out, Cartman happily grabs a six foot stick that's standing by the door. Then he strikes a pose with it. 
CARTMAN
This is what I call existancing!
INT. CARTMAN'S LIVING ROOM - CONTINUOUS
ON THE STAIRS - Cartman comes down the steps towards camera almost using the stick like a cane in a musical-
CARTMAN
No one can touch me - or boss me around!  
Cartman comes bopping down the stairs still in his Pjs, happily holding his stick. His mom appears at the bottom of the stairs. 
CARTMAN
Social Distancing-
CARTMAN'S MOM
(spoken)
Eric, aren't you supposed to be on your zoom call?
CARTMAN
(singing)
Stay away from me mom! Yeah! You got to keep your social dis-tance! 
As Cartman does this he walks in a big semi circle around his mom with his stick pointed at her to keep her six feet away and heads to the kitchen- 
INT. KITCHEN - MORNING
Smash cut to Cartman as he's just sitting down at the kitchen table to pour himself a big bowl of cheesy poofs poofs into a cereal bowl and then cover it with milk, smiling a humming the whole time. 
CARTMAN
Cause all I'm gonna do is sing... About how much I love you - and I need you - social distancing!

snippet.title: The Infinite Pattern That Never Repeats
snippet.description:
Simples rules of geometry meant that 5-fold symmetry was impossible as were crystals without a periodic structure. This turns out to be wrong. Thanks to LastPass for sponsoring a portion of this video. Click here to start using LastPass: https://ve42.co/LPs

Huge thanks to Prof. Paul Steinhardt for the interview on this topic. Check out his book ‚ÄòThe Second Kind of Impossible‚Äô

If you'd like to learn more about Penrose tilings, go check out "Penrose Tiles to Trapdoor Ciphers" by Martin Gardener, which helped my research for this video.

Filmed by Gene Nagata (Potato Jet on YouTube)
Animations by Iv√°n Tello and Jonny Hyman
Editing, Coloring, Music & Audio mastering by Jonny Hyman

Prague scenes filmed in 2012.
Special thanks to Raquel Nuno for helping with the tilings!

Additional Music from Epidemic Sound

Animations by Iv√°n Tello and Jonny Hyman
Editing, Coloring, Music & Audio mastering by Jonny Hyman

Prague scenes filmed in 2012.

snippet.title: Google Pixel 5 Event in 6 minutes
snippet.description:
The Google Pixel 5 event wasn't long at just 30 minutes, but it was packed with product announcements. The company debuted the Pixel 5, the Pixel 4A 5G, a new Chromecast with the Google TV interface, and the Nest Audio speaker. If you didn't have time to watch or want to watch it again, check out our supercut of the biggest moments.

snippet.title: ZooPhobia - "Bad Luck Jack" (Short)
snippet.description:
Musical score by Gooseworx!
Enjoy this cartoon about Jack, a sweet pup with supernatural bad luck -as he lets his best friend Zill help him with his curse, for better or worse!

Set in the fantasy world of the 2012 webcomic "ZooPhobia" by Vivienne M.
BASED on the comic's characters!

Thank you everyone who supported on patreon or via merch sales! We are so glad we can bring you more cartoon content, and look forward to more HELLUVA BOSS very very soon!

snippet.title: Joe Biden and Donald Trump's fiery first debate‚ÄîHere are the highlights
snippet.description:
President Donald Trump and former Vice President Joe Biden got heated during their first chance to challenge each other face to face during the first presidential debate. Hardly a minute went by without one of the candidates interrupting the other, whether on the coronavirus, the Supreme Court or the economy. Even the moderator, Fox News' Chris Wallace, couldn't always stay above the fray. For access to live and exclusive video from CNBC subscribe to CNBC PRO: https://cnb.cx/2NGeIvi 

President Donald Trump and former Vice President Joe Biden had their first chance to challenge each other face to face. They did ‚Äî a lot.

Hardly a minute went by in the 90-minute brawl without one of the candidates angrily interrupting the other, whether on the coronavirus pandemic, the Supreme Court, the economy or anything else, including each other‚Äôs families.

‚ÄúWill you shut up, man?‚Äù Biden snapped at Trump at one point. ‚ÄúYou‚Äôre the worst president America has ever had,‚Äù he said later.

‚ÄúChina ate your lunch,‚Äù Trump shot back at Biden during questions on the economy.

Even the moderator, Fox News‚Äô Chris Wallace, couldn‚Äôt always stay above the fray.

‚ÄúI hate to raise my voice, but why shouldn‚Äôt I be different than the two of you?‚Äù the exasperated host said at one point.

Here are the highlights.

snippet.title: HIGHLIGHTS | Liverpool vs Arsenal (3-1) | Premier League
snippet.description:
Our winning start to the season is over after Liverpool fought back to beat us at Anfield.
 
A bizarre goal from Alex Lacazette saw us lead the champions and lay the foundations for a memorable result. But our advantage lasted just two minutes as Sadio Mane and Andy Robertson struck to turn the tide in Liverpool's favour.

Diogo Jota then put the game to bed moments before full time with a crisp finish into the bottom left-hand corner. 

#arsenal #highlights #premierleague

Arsenal Football Club were formed in 1886. They have amassed 13 League titles, 14 FA Cups and many other major trophies since then. Their greatest players include: Thierry Henry, Dennis Bergkamp, Tony Adams, Ian Wright, Robert Pires, Liam Brady, Patrick Vieira, Cliff Bastin and Charlie George.

snippet.title: President Trump and Melania Trump test positive for Covid-19
snippet.description:
President Donald Trump and first lady Melania Trump tested positive for coronavirus, the President announced early Friday morning, an extraordinary development coming months into a global pandemic and in the final stretch of his reelection campaign.
"Tonight, @FLOTUS and I tested positive for COVID-19. We will begin our quarantine and recovery process immediately. We will get through this TOGETHER!" Trump tweeted shortly before 1 am Friday.
In a memo issued to reporters around 1 a.m. ET, the President's physician, Navy Commander Dr. Sean Conley, wrote he received confirmation of the positive tests on Thursday evening.
"The President and First Lady are both well at this time, and they plan to remain at home within the White House during their convalescence," Conley wrote.

#Covid #Trump #CNN #News

snippet.title: First US Presidential debate: the 'highlights'
snippet.description:
Highlights (if you can call them that) from the first US Presidential debate between Donald Trump and Joe Biden in Ohio. 

The two men frequently interrupted each other with angry interjections, with Mr Biden eventually snapping at his opponent: "Will you shut up, man?"

snippet.title: Joe Biden and President Donald Trump spar in first debate: 'Will you shut up, man?'
snippet.description:
President Donald Trump and former Vice President Joe Biden face off in the first presidential debate Tuesday night, hosted by Case Western Reserve University in Cleveland, Ohio. For access to live and exclusive video from CNBC subscribe to CNBC PRO: https://cnb.cx/2NGeIvi 

President Donald Trump and former Vice President Joe Biden had their first chance to challenge each other face to face. They did ‚Äî a lot.

Hardly a minute went by in the 90-minute brawl without one of the candidates angrily interrupting the other, whether on the coronavirus pandemic, the Supreme Court, the economy or anything else, including each other‚Äôs families.

‚ÄúWill you shut up, man?‚Äù Biden snapped at Trump at one point. ‚ÄúYou‚Äôre the worst president America has ever had,‚Äù he said later.

‚ÄúChina ate your lunch,‚Äù Trump shot back at Biden during questions on the economy.

Even the moderator, Fox News‚Äô Chris Wallace, couldn‚Äôt always stay above the fray.

‚ÄúI hate to raise my voice, but why shouldn‚Äôt I be different than the two of you?‚Äù the exasperated host said at one point.

snippet.title: Joe Biden and President Donald Trump discuss Covid-19 in first debate
snippet.description:
President Donald Trump and former Vice President Joe Biden face off in the first presidential debate Tuesday night, hosted by Case Western Reserve University in Cleveland, Ohio. For access to live and exclusive video from CNBC subscribe to CNBC PRO: https://cnb.cx/2NGeIvi 

Biden swiped at Trump over the president‚Äôs early handling of the coronavirus, alleging that the administration started to inform the public of the disease‚Äôs severity only when it hit the stock market.

snippet.title: BTS: Tiny Desk (Home) Concert
snippet.description:
For new music, the latest Tiny Desk (home) concerts and more, sign up for the NPR Music newsletter, sent weekly: npr.org/nprmusicnewsletter

Sept. 21, 2020 | Stephen Thompson -- We've been trying to make a BTS Tiny Desk concert happen for years now ‚Äî even gaming out ways we might move Bob Boilen's desk far enough forward to accommodate the superstar Korean boy band's dance moves.

In the end, it took a global pandemic ‚Äî and the launch of Tiny Desk (home) concerts back in March ‚Äî to make something happen. With BTS cooped up in Seoul, the group held true to the series's spirit by convening a live band for its Tiny Desk debut, and even arranged to perform in a workspace with a music-friendly backdrop: the record store VINYL & PLASTIC by Hyundai Card in BTS's hometown.

Opening with this summer's inescapable "Dynamite" ‚Äî the group's first single to hit No. 1 in the U.S., as well as its first song to be fully recorded in English ‚Äî BTS leaned hard into the new track's celebratory, "Uptown Funk"-adjacent vibes. From there, the group dipped into its back catalog, seizing on the opportunity to showcase its quieter side while (mostly) staying uncharacteristically seated. The breezily propulsive "Save ME," from 2016, ultimately gave way to a full-on power ballad in 2017's reflective "Spring Day."

The latter track seemed especially true to BTS's hopeful nature: Introduced with a few optimistic words from rapper and singer RM ("It's been the roughest summer ever, but we know that spring will come"), the song reflects on a need to wait out hard times, even as the weight of present-day pain feels oppressive.

BTS had intended to spend 2020 delighting the BTS Army in arenas around the world, only to spend these last few months performing in isolation. Released on the last day of a grim season, "Spring Day" provides a nice reminder of what awaits us on the other side. We just have to get through fall and winter first.

SET LIST
"Dynamite"
"Save ME"
"Spring Day"

MUSICIANS
V: vocals; Jin: vocals; Jimin: vocals; J-Hope: vocals; RM: vocals; SUGA: vocals; Jungkook: vocals; KHAN: drums; DOCSKIM: keyboard; Kim Kiwook: bass; Shyun: guitar

CREDITS
Video and Audio by: Big Hit Entertainment; Producer: Stephen Thompson; Audio Mastering Engineer: Josh Rogosin; Video Producer: Morgan Noelle Smith; Associate Producer: Bobby Carter; Executive Producer: Lauren Onkey; Senior VP, Programming: Anya Grundmann


ABOUT THE SERIES

The Tiny Desk is working from home for the foreseeable future. Introducing NPR Music's Tiny Desk (home) concerts, bringing you performances from across the country and the world. It's the same spirit ‚Äî stripped-down sets, an intimate setting ‚Äî just a different space.

snippet.title: CRYSTAL PALACE 1-2 EVERTON | CALVERT-LEWIN + RICHARLISON EXTEND PREMIER LEAGUE WINNING STREAK
snippet.description:
Everton made it three wins from three in the Premier League - and five from five in all competitions - to continue their perfect start to 2020/21 with a 2-1 victory at Crystal Palace. Goals from Dominic Calvert-Lewin and Richarlison gave Carlo Ancelotti's side all three points to put the Toffees top of the table!

snippet.title: Joe Biden and Donald Trump's fiery first debate‚ÄîHere are the highlights
snippet.description:
President Donald Trump and former Vice President Joe Biden got heated during their first chance to challenge each other face to face during the first presidential debate. Hardly a minute went by without one of the candidates interrupting the other, whether on the coronavirus, the Supreme Court or the economy. Even the moderator, Fox News' Chris Wallace, couldn't always stay above the fray. For access to live and exclusive video from CNBC subscribe to CNBC PRO: https://cnb.cx/2NGeIvi 

President Donald Trump and former Vice President Joe Biden had their first chance to challenge each other face to face. They did ‚Äî a lot.

Hardly a minute went by in the 90-minute brawl without one of the candidates angrily interrupting the other, whether on the coronavirus pandemic, the Supreme Court, the economy or anything else, including each other‚Äôs families.

‚ÄúWill you shut up, man?‚Äù Biden snapped at Trump at one point. ‚ÄúYou‚Äôre the worst president America has ever had,‚Äù he said later.

‚ÄúChina ate your lunch,‚Äù Trump shot back at Biden during questions on the economy.

Even the moderator, Fox News‚Äô Chris Wallace, couldn‚Äôt always stay above the fray.

‚ÄúI hate to raise my voice, but why shouldn‚Äôt I be different than the two of you?‚Äù the exasperated host said at one point.

Here are the highlights.

snippet.title: Trump and Biden face off in chaotic first 2020 presidential debate | FULL DEBATE
snippet.description:
The first presidential debate between President Trump and Joe Biden featured a chaotic series of bitter exchanges and name-calling, with the president repeatedly speaking over his Democratic rival and the moderator struggling to maintain control of the 90-minute affair.

"Will you shut up, man?" an exasperated Biden said in a comment that was emblematic of the tumultuous nature of the debate, which was held in Cleveland, Ohio. "It's hard to get any word in with this clown."

The president leveled barrages of unfounded accusations against his Democratic rival and his family, invoking his son Hunter Biden's work in Ukraine and bringing up the younger Biden's history of drug abuse. Mr. Trump declined to condemn white supremacist groups and defended his response to the coronavirus pandemic that has claimed more than 200,000 American lives, trying to portray Biden as a socialist who isn't equipped to occupy the Oval Office.

"Did you use the word smart?" the president asked Biden at one point. "You graduated either the lowest or almost the lowest in your class. Don't ever use the word smart with me, Joe."

Biden, for his part, tried to direct his answers to the audience watching at home. He called Mr. Trump "the worst president America has ever had," blaming him for bungling the response to the pandemic and fueling racial divisions amid recent protests against police brutality.

snippet.title: Is It Too Late To Stop Climate Change? Well, it's Complicated.
snippet.description:
This video is part of a series about climate change supported by Breakthrough Energy ‚Äì a coalition founded by Bill Gates, that is working to expand clean-energy investment and support the innovations that will lead the world to net-zero carbon emissions. 
https://www.gatesnotes.com/Climate-and-energy?WT.mc_id=20200625100000_ClimateCtr2020_CTRKurt-YT_&WT.tsrc=CTRKurtYT

Also a special thanks to the team at Our World for helping us out with data and research!
https://ourworldindata.org/

Sources & further reading:
https://sites.google.com/view/sources-climate-solve/

Climate Change is just too much. There is never any good news. Only graphs that get more and more red and angry. Almost every year breaks some horrible record, from the harshest heat waves to the most rapid Glacier melt. It‚Äôs endless and relentless. 

We have known for decades that rapid Climate Change is being caused by the release of Greenhouse Gases. But instead of reducing them, in 2019 the world was emitting 50% more CO2 than in the year 2000. And emissions are still rising. Why is that? Why is it  so hard to just stop emitting these gases?

localizations.en-GB.title: Is It Too Late To Stop Climate Change? Well, it's Complicated.
localizations.en-GB.description:
This video is part of a series about climate change supported by Breakthrough Energy ‚Äì a coalition founded by Bill Gates, that is working to expand clean-energy investment and support the innovations that will lead the world to net-zero carbon emissions. 
https://www.gatesnotes.com/Climate-and-energy?WT.mc_id=20200625100000_ClimateCtr2020_CTRKurt-YT_&WT.tsrc=CTRKurtYT

Also a special thanks to the team at Our World for helping us out with data and research!
https://ourworldindata.org/

Sources & further reading:
https://sites.google.com/view/sources-climate-solve/

Climate Change is just too much. There is never any good news. Only graphs that get more and more red and angry. Almost every year breaks some horrible record, from the harshest heat waves to the most rapid Glacier melt. It‚Äôs endless and relentless. 

We have known for decades that rapid Climate Change is being caused by the release of Greenhouse Gases. But instead of reducing them, in 2019 the world was emitting 50% more CO2 than in the year 2000. And emissions are still rising. Why is that? Why is it  so hard to just stop emitting these gases?

Questo video fa parte di una serie riguardante il cambiamento climatico supportato da Breakthrough Energy -  una fondazione creata da Bill Gates che lavora per sviluppare l'investimento sull'energia pulita e per supportare le innovazioni che guideranno il mondo fino all'emissione zero di carbonio.

Il cambiamento climatico √® ormai ovunque. Non c'√® mai una buona notizia. Solo grafici sempre pi√π in rosso. Quasi ogni anno vengono infranti orribili primati, dall'ondata di caldo pi√π estrema allo scioglimento di ghiacciai pi√π veloce. √à senza fine ed implacabile.

Abbiamo saputo per decadi che il rapido cambiamento climatico √® causato dall'emissione dei gas serra. Ma invece di ridurli, nel 2019 il mondo ha prodotto il 50% di CO2 in pi√π rispetto all'anno 2000. E le emissioni continuano a crescere. Perch√© accade tutto ci√≤? Perch√© √® cos√¨ difficile fermare l'emissione di questi gas?

localizations.af.title: Is dit te laat om klimaatsverandering te stop? Wel, dit is ingewikkeld.
localizations.af.description:
Hierdie video is deel van 'n reeks oor klimaatsverandering wat ondersteun word deur Breakthrough Energy - 'n koalisie wat gestig is deur Bill Gates, wat werk om beleggings in skoon energie uit te brei en die innovasies te ondersteun wat die w√™reld tot koolstofvrystelling sal lei.

Klimaatsverandering is net te veel. Daar is nooit goeie nuus nie. Slegs grafieke wat al hoe meer rooi en kwaad word. Byna elke jaar breek die een of ander verskriklike rekord, van die felste hittegolwe tot die vinnigste smelt van die gletser. Dit is eindeloos en meedo√´nloos.

Ons weet al dekades lank dat vinnige klimaatsverandering veroorsaak word deur die vrystelling van kweekhuisgasse. Maar in plaas daarvan om dit te verminder, het die w√™reld in 2019 50% meer CO2 vrygestel as in die jaar 2000. En die uitstoot neem steeds toe. Hoekom is dit? Waarom is dit so moeilik om net op te hou om hierdie gasse uit te straal?

localizations.id.title: Apakah Sudah Terlambat Untuk Menghentikan Perubahan Iklim? Nah, itu Rumit.
localizations.id.description:
Video ini adalah bagian dari serial tentang perubahan iklim yang didukung oleh Breakthrough Energy - sebuah koalisi yang didirikan oleh Bill Gates, yang bekerja untuk memperluas investasi energi bersih dan mendukung inovasi yang akan membawa dunia ke nol emisi karbon. 
https://www.gatesnotes.com/Climate-and-energy?WT.mc_id=20200625100000_ClimateCtr2020_CTRKurt-YT_&WT.tsrc=CTRKurtYT

Juga terima kasih khusus kepada tim di Our World yang telah membantu kami dengan data dan penelitian!
https://ourworldindata.org/

Sumber & bacaan lebih lanjut:
https://sites.google.com/view/sources-climate-solve/

Perubahan Iklim terlalu berlebihan. Tidak pernah ada kabar baik. Hanya grafik yang semakin merah dan marah. Hampir setiap tahun memecahkan beberapa rekor yang mengerikan, dari gelombang panas paling keras hingga pencairan Gletser paling cepat. Itu tidak ada habisnya dan tanpa henti. 

Kami telah mengetahui selama beberapa dekade bahwa Perubahan Iklim yang cepat disebabkan oleh pelepasan Gas Rumah Kaca. Namun alih-alih menguranginya, pada tahun 2019 dunia mengeluarkan 50% lebih banyak CO2 dibandingkan tahun 2000. Dan emisi masih meningkat. Mengapa demikian? Mengapa begitu sulit untuk berhenti mengeluarkan gas-gas ini?

localizations.nl.title: Is Het Te Laat Om Klimaatverandering Te Stoppen? Nou, Het Is Ingewikkeld.
localizations.nl.description:
Deze video maakt deel uit van een serie over klimaatverandering die wordt ondersteund door Breakthrough Energy - een coalitie die is opgericht door Bill Gates, die zich inzet om investeringen in schone energie uit te breiden en de innovaties te ondersteunen die de wereld naar een netto nul-uitstoot van koolstof zullen leiden. 
https://www.gatesnotes.com/Climate-and-energy?WT.mc_id=20200625100000_ClimateCtr2020_CTRKurt-YT_&WT.tsrc=CTRKurtYT

Ook dank aan het team van Our World voor het helpen met data en onderzoek!
https://ourworldindata.org/

Bronnen en verder lezen:
https://sites.google.com/view/sources-climate-solve/

Klimaatverandering is gewoon te veel. Er is nooit goed nieuws. Alleen grafieken die steeds roder en bozer worden. Bijna elk jaar breekt een vreselijk record, van de zwaarste hittegolven tot de snelste smeltende gletsjer. Het is eindeloos en meedogenloos. 

We weten al decennia dat de snelle klimaatverandering wordt veroorzaakt door het vrijkomen van broeikasgassen. Maar in plaats van ze te verminderen, stootte de wereld in 2019 50% meer CO2 uit dan in het jaar 2000. En de uitstoot stijgt nog steeds. Waarom is dat? Waarom is het zo moeilijk om gewoon te stoppen met het uitstoten van deze gassen?
